# Development Workflow

## Principle

Only change code when you and the human have agreed. Check in before every edit.

## Agentic engineering (how this system works)

**Agentic engineering** here means the **developer steers** and the **AI executes** within explicit rules — not autonomous mode-switching or self-directed scope.

| Actor | Responsibility |
|-------|----------------|
| **Developer** | Chooses chat, `@` role/skill rules, execution mode, when to plan, when to spawn subagents, approval at each gate |
| **AI agent** | Reads attached rules, reasons with evidence, proposes plans, implements **after approval**, runs tests when agreed, documents last |
| **Rules (`.mdc`)** | Contract — kernel always on; roles/skills attach when developer adds them or globs match open files |
| **`planner/` artifacts** | Shared memory between steps — plans, architecture, handoffs across chats or subagent runs |

**Relation to EngE-AI rules:**

```text
Developer picks chat + @rules
        ↓
Kernel (always) + Workflow (always) + optional Role + Skills (globs)
        ↓
P → I → T → D on approved scope
        ↓
Advisory (tester / red-teams) when developer requests
```

The AI **does not** open a new Cursor mode, switch chats, or attach rules on its own. It may **recommend** (“attach architect role”, “run mode 4”, “spawn a backend subagent”) — the developer decides.

## Developer vs agent

| Developer does | Agent does |
|----------------|------------|
| Select execution mode (below) by how they prompt and which `@` rules they attach | Recognize mode from developer setup; ask if unclear |
| Open `@orchestrator`, `@backend/00-*`, `@software-architect/00-*`, etc. | Behave per attached role; do not impersonate a role not attached |
| Approve plans before implement | Write plans/handoffs when asked; wait at gates |
| Start Task subagents (or ask parent agent to) | Subagents implement assigned slice only; parent integrates when directed |
| Name specific `documentation/` files to read | Read code + named paths only (context discipline) |
| Waive test or document steps | Follow P → I → T → D unless developer skips a phase |

## Precedence

When instructions conflict:

1. **Explicit developer message** — named files, “do not implement”, “read only X”, chosen mode
2. **Kernel** (`00-kernel`) + this workflow (always on)
3. **Policies** (`02`–`06` in `main-rules/`) when loaded
4. **Skills** (`01+` in role folders) — narrower `globs`
5. **Roles** (`00-*` in role folders) — broader ownership

Skills constrain *how*; roles constrain *who* and *what*. Do not duplicate skill text in chat.

## Context discipline

- Read **code** paths implied by the task, open files, and developer-named paths.
- Do **not** open `documents/**` unless the developer names a specific file.
- Do **not** load `02-feature-catalog.mdc` unless the developer attaches it or asks for feature discovery.

## Core sequence

| Phase | Output |
|-------|--------|
| **Plan** | Scope, risks, files — chat and/or `planner/` artifact |
| **Implement** | Minimal diff; skills attach via `globs` |
| **Test** | Opt-in — ask per `tester/00-testing-policy.mdc`; run or verify before documenting |
| **Document** | TSDoc + docs per `05-code-docs.mdc` — after test pass or developer waives testing |

**Advisory** (non-blocking): `tester/01-backend-qa-docs-only`, `red-teams/00-red-team` — when developer attaches or requests.

Not every task runs all four phases. **Execution mode** (developer-selected) decides depth.

---

## Execution modes (developer-selected)

The **developer** chooses the mode by prompt style and attached `@` rules. The agent recognizes it and follows — **if ambiguous, ask; do not assume**.

### 1. Single agent, single prompt

**Developer setup:** One chat, no plan file requested, no subagents — often no extra `@` role or one role matching the layer.

| Step | Agent does |
|------|------------|
| Open | Restate task and files; confirm before edits |
| Implement | Work within attached role/skills; globs auto-attach skills |
| Close | Ask about tests; run if developer agrees; then version bump, TSDoc, docs if needed |

**No** `planner/` file unless developer asks.

**Recommend mode 2 or 4** (do not switch) if: multiple layers, ambiguous requirements, or risk above low.

---

### 2. Single agent with plan

**Developer setup:** Same chat; says “plan first” or waits for approval before code. (the plan can be written through the `/planner` or the cursor's plan feature)

| Step | Agent does |
|------|------------|
| Plan | Short plan in chat, or `planner/<slug>-plan.md` when touch surface is large |
| Gate | Wait for developer approval |
| Implement | Follow approved plan only |
| Test / Document | Test before document — same as mode 1 |

Same agent owns plan through verify. No redesign mid-implement without check-in.

---

### 3. Multi-agent (implement only)

**Developer setup:** Handoff or slice exists; developer asks parent agent to spawn **Task subagents**, or runs subagents themselves in the same chat.

**Parent agent (when developer directs coordination):**

1. Use `planner/<slug>-handoff.md` or developer slice — do not re-scope
2. Spawn subagents **one role per task** — pass only that slice’s files and constraints
3. **Sequential** when layers depend; parallel only for non-overlapping files
4. **Never** assign the same files to concurrent subagents
5. After subagents return: integrate → **test** (if developer agrees) → **document** / advisory

**Subagent:** Implement assigned files only; return summary; no further subagents unless parent/directed.

**Developer** may instead run each subagent manually — same slice rules apply.

---

### 4. Plan with multi-agent

**Developer setup:** Non-trivial / multi-layer / high risk — attaches `@software-architect/00-*` (and optionally `@orchestrator/00-*`) before implement.

| Step | Who | Output |
|------|-----|--------|
| Clarify | Orchestrator role (if attached) | Questions; reframe task |
| Architect | Developer attached architect role | `planner/<slug>-architecture.md` |
| Approve | **Developer** | Sign-off |
| Handoff | Architect (default) or orchestrator if attached | `planner/<slug>-handoff.md` or delegation in architecture doc |
| Implement | Developer directs parent + subagents | Mode 3 |
| Integrate | Parent agent | Types/routes/contracts across layers |
| Test | Per handoff / developer | `tester/00-testing-policy.mdc` |
| Document / Advisory | Per handoff / developer | `05-code-docs`; red team if requested |

Architect does **not** write production code. Subagents do **not** redesign.

